-- Nice Advances to Three-Year High, Narrows Gap With U.S. Shares
-- B y   S h o s h a n n a   S o l o m o n
-- 2012-03-22T08:48:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-22/nice-advances-to-three-year-high-narrows-gap-with-u-s-shares.html
Nice Systems Ltd. (NICE) , an Israeli maker
of analytical telecommunications software, rallied to the
highest level since November 2007, narrowing the gap with its
U.S.-traded shares.  The  shares  added 2.8 percent to 141.40 shekels, or the
equivalent of $37.72, the highest level since November 2007 at
10:20 a.m. in  Tel Aviv . The stock rose 4.3 percent to close at
$37.98 in  New York  yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shoshanna Solomon in Tel Aviv at 
 ssolomon22@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
